Saint. It was done in such an instant of time, it is impossible to give an account of it, except I had stood on purpose to look at it; for I believe from the time of her coming into the shop, and the wound being given, it did not last above a minuet. I ran to Dr. Tolmin's, he was not at home; his son came;
William Downing
ran for another surgeon; but when I returned Oliphant was dead. I believe he was dead in the space of 4 or 5 minutes.

Woolf. They are under Hungerford-market;
David Davis
went there and I held the candle whilst he fitted the keys.

Woolf. He said, I deliver these keys into your hands; don't you deliver them to any one, for I trust my life in your hands;
Abraham Davis
always kept them in his custody.

Woolf. No, I had not; I don't know whether it was sold or not. The next we got might be in the same week; sometimes we took twice and sometimes three times a week;
Abraham Davis
used always to go with me.
